        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Those of you saying that the Sleeper is involved in a quest are most likely right.  The quest is not possible yet though.  The only one who can kill the Sleeper is the chosen avatar of Mithaniel Marr.  He will weild the weapon of the god, which I believe is called the truthbringer, granted to him by Trakanon.  He will also be the 4th champion of Trakanon (that's how he gets the sword) and will be able to slay the Sleeper with on fell blow.  So yeah he's involved in the biggest quest in the game.  You can't do it though, at least not yet.  I believe that as the 4th champion of Trakanon he will also have the other items Trakanon had granted his previous champions.    The reason the Sleeper is in the tomb in the first place is because the beast is so damn strong.  Even the wurmqueen herself feared Kerafym's power.  That of course being where the dragon goes after awakened, to the Plane of Sky to challenge the wurmqueen.  I may have a couple of this wrong but that's the jist of it.  I would say no, no player(s) could ever kill Kerafym barring that some one is finally chosen as the 4th champion of Trakanon.</P><P>Crilk<BR>56 master of the order of Fist and Tail/Lost Circle<BR>Druzzil Ro</P><P>Chakru<BR>35 studen of dark heraldry</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
