         I just figured I should post a little lore on the Sleeper that I've gathered:</P><P>According to Dragon laws, dragons of different colors are forbiden to mate. What I have heard is it was two other red and blue dragons, not Vox and Naggy, Vox and Naggy tried but Veeshan stopped them before they could. Now after the Sleeper was born, Veeshan banished the two dragons and put Kerafyrm to sleep because she feared its power. She also sent 4 warders to keep anyone from awaking the Sleeper.</P><P>Now think about this for a second. If they make the creator of the dragons, Veeshan, who is as big as Norrath and whose CLAWS made the deep chasms in WW and GD, is afraid of the Sleepers power, then how the hell are we supposed to kill it?</P><P>What I think is after PoP comes out there will probably be some quest to activate the Sword of Truth, probably respawn the Sleeper or have a quest to trigger it (as most should know, the Sleeper goes to kill Lord Yelinak and just despawns, so that doesn't exactly make the Sleeper dead...)</P><P>Still, even if the Sword of Truth is ever usable, it might not make much of a difference if the Sleeper can AoE DT...we can hope I guess</P><P>Baritz Shadowreaver<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=278788" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=278788</a></P><P>If you named your character LuckyCharms, mobs would keep saying "I'll teach you to interfere with me LuckyCharms!"<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
